of-how-elon-musks-relationship-with-trump-imploded-2025-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epublic%20feud%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20House%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhouse-passes-doge-cuts-rescission-npr-pbs-pepfar-2025-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Enarrowly%20approved%20the%20cuts%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20in%20part%20identified%20by%20Musk%20and%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdoge-department-of-government-efficiency%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EWhite%20House%20DOGE%20Office%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20earlier%20this%20month.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20administration's%20troubles%20were%20evident%20at%20a%20Senate%20Appropriations%20Committee%20hearing%20on%20Wednesday.%20Lawmakers%20in%20both%20parties%20highlighted%20the%20potential%20negative%20impacts%20of%20clawing%20back%20the%20funding%20as%20they%20heard%20testimony%20from%20Russell%20Vought%2C%20the%20director%20of%20the%20White%20House%20Office%20of%20Management%20and%20Budget.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20have%20Native%20American%20radio%20stations%20in%20South%20Dakota.%20They%20get%20their%20funding%20through%20NPR%2C%2090-some%20percent%20of%20what%20they%20use%2C%26quot%3B%20Republican%20Sen.%20Mike%20Rounds%20of%20South%20Dakota%20said%20at%20the%20hearing.%20%26quot%3BThey%20will%20not%20continue%20to%20exist%20if%20we%20don't%20find%20a%20way%20to%20take%20care%20of%20their%20needs.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERepublican%20Sen.%20Susan%20Collins%20of%20Maine%2C%20the%20committee%20chair%2C%20also%20raised%20concerns%20about%20the%20%241.1%20billion%20in%20public%20broadcasting%20cuts.%20Another%20moderate%20Republican%2C%20Sen.%20Lisa%20Murkowski%20of%20Alaska%2C%20has%20previously%20said%20that%20she's%20opposed%20to%20the%20cuts%20because%20rural%20Alaskan%20communities%20depend%20on%20the%20funding.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESeveral%20GOP%20lawmakers%20are%20also%20concerned%20about%20the%20%248.3%20billion%20in%20foreign%20aid%20cut