n%20the%20making.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBack%20in%202009%2C%20unidentified%20officers%20with%20the%20Defense%20Threat%20Reduction%20Agency%2C%20which%20specializes%20in%20deeply%20buried%20underground%20targets%2C%20were%20briefed%20on%20a%20major%20construction%20project%20in%20Iran%20%E2%80%94%20specifically%20Fordow%2C%20which%20Caine%20described%20as%20a%20%26quot%3Bcritical%20element%26quot%3B%20of%20Tehran's%20covert%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsatellite-images-damage-iran-fordow-nuclear-site-after-us-strikes-2025-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Enuclear%20weapons%20program%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20DTRA%20officers%20studied%20the%20Fordow%20site%2C%20which%20is%20built%20into%20a%20mountain%2C%20closely%20for%20years.%20Caine%20said%20they%20eventually%20realized%20that%20the%20US%20didn't%20have%20a%20weapon%20that%20could%20be%20used%20to%20attack%20the%20facility%2C%20so%20they%20started%20working%20with%20the%20defense%20industry%20partners%20like%20Boeing%20and%20Northrop%20Grumman%20to%20further%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fisrael-trying-to-destroy-iran-nuclear-program-wont-be-easy-2025-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Edevelop%20the%20MOP%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20bomb%20was%20part%20of%20a%20DTRA%20technology%20demonstration%20program%20until%202010%2C%20when%20the%20weapon%20became%20a%20part%20of%20the%20Air%20Force's%20Quick%20Reaction%20Capability%20Program%2C%20per%20the%20air%20service.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222551%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20US%20Air%20Force%20B-2%20Spirit%20Bomber%20against%20a%20gray%20sky.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6859a82485e81483682c96b9%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221697%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20GBU-57%20can%20only%20be%20carried%20by%20B-2%20bombers.%3Cp%3EUS%20Air%20National%20Guard%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20massive%20bomb%20was%20tested%20hundreds%20of%20times.%20Many%20full-scale%20munitions%20were%20dropped%20on%20%26quot%3Bextremely%26quot%3B%20realistic%20targets%20with%20the%20goal%20of%20having%20a%20weapon%20that%20the%20US%20could%20use%20against%20Fordow%20at%20a%20time%20and%20place%20of%20its%20choosing%2C%20Caine%20explained.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20day%20came%20just%20a%20few%20days%20ago%2C%20when%20President%20Donald%20Trump%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fus-struck-iran-with-most-elusive-weapons-stealth-bombers-submarine-2025-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eordered%20the%20B-2s%20to%20bomb%20Fordow%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2278a76afc-e236-4bbf-b7c3-8ca12a1cda9a%5C%22%3EStrikes%20on%20Iran%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20extremely%20heavy%20MOP%20is%20around%2020.5%20feet%20long%20and%20has%20a%20diameter%20of%2031.5%20inches.%20The%20warhead%20alone%20weighs%206%2C000%20pounds%2C%20and%20it%20can%20penetrate%20deeply%20buried%20facilities%20up%20to%20around%20200%20feet%20deep.%20The%20B-2%20is%20the%20only%20operational%20aircraft%20that%20can%20carry%20the%20weapon%2C%20storing%20two%20internally%20to%20preserve%20stealth.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECaine%20said%20that%20the%20MOP%20is%20made%20of%20steel%2C%20explosives%2C%20and%20a%20fuse%20programmed%20to%20achieve%20a%20specific%20effect%20inside%20Fordow.%20Each%20bomb%20had%20a%20unique%20impact%20angle%2C%20arrival%2C%20final%20heading%2C%20and%20fuse%20setting%2C%20which%20determines%20when%20the%20weapon%20would%20explode.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20longer%20fuse%20creates%20a%20delay%2C%20meaning%20the%20MOP%20can%20penetrate%20deeper%20into%20the%20target%20before%20it%20explodes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222864%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20GBU-57%20test%20in%20a%20video%20shared%20by%20the%20Department%20of%20Defense.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F685d662085e81483682cd1a0%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221664%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20GBU-57%20bunker-buster%20bomb%20can%20penetrate%20hardened%20bunkers.%3Cp%3EDepartment%20of%20Defense%2FScreengrab%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EFordow%20had%20sets%20of%20three%20holes%20%E2%80%94%20a%20main%20exhaust%20shaft%20and%20two%20additional%20ventilation%20shafts%20%E2%80%94%20visible%20on%20the%20surface.%20Caine%20said%20that%20in%20the%20days%20leading%20up%20to%20the%20attack%2C%20Iran%20attempted%20to%20cover%20the%20shafts%20with%20concrete.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETalking%20about%20one%20target%20point%2C%20which%20was%20hit%20with%20six%20of%20the%20large%20GBU-57%20bunker-busters%2C%20Caine%20said%20that%20the%20first%20MOP%20%26quot%3Bforcibly%20removed%26quot%3B%20the%20concrete%20cap%2C%20exposing%20the%20main%20shaft.%20The%20next%20four%20MOPs%20entered%20that%20shaft%2C%20traveling%20toward%20critical%20Fordow%20facilities%20at%20speeds%20faster%20than%201%2C000%20feet%20per%20second%20and%20exploding%20inside.%20The%20sixth%20bomb%20dropped%20was%20a%20flexible%20option%20if%20something%20didn't%20work%20the%20way%20it%20was%20intended.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BUnlike%20a%20normal%20surface%20bomb%2C%20you%20won't%20see%20an%20impact%20crater%2C%20because%20they're%20designed%20to%20deeply%20bury%20and%20then%20function%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsatellite-images-damage-iran-fordow-nuclear-site-after-us-strikes-2025-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3ESatellite%20imagery%3C%2Fa%3E%20showed%20the%20holes%20where%20the%20MOPs%20penetrated%20the%20surface%20at%20Fordow%2C%20but%20not%20a%20substantial%20impact%20crater%20at%20the%20site.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECaine%20said%20all%20six%20weapons%20dropped%20on%20the%20vents%20went%20where%20they%20were%20meant%20to%20go.%20He%20shared%20that%20the%20%26quot%3Bprimary%20kill%20mechanism%26quot%3B%20at%20the%20site%20was%20a%20mixture%20of%20blast%20and%20overpressure%2C%20which%20would%20have%20ripped%20through%20the%20open